  section#press.content-section.press
    .page-contain
      blockquote.quote
        p.
          Hack for LA is a great example of how we can harness technology and our city's creativity to solve everyday problems. As Mayor, I will closely partner with our tech industry to create jobs and bring innovation to City Hall so government works faster and more efficiently.
        cite.type-h4 Mayor Eric Garcetti
        img(src='/images/quote-garcetti.jpg').quote-tmb
      h2 Press
      ul.news-cards.unstyled-list
        each item in news
          li.news-card
            .news-card-inner
              .news-body
                h4.news-title
                  a(href=item.url)= item.title
                p= item.publication

  section#about.content-section.about
    .page-contain
      h2 Want to know more about Hack for LA?
      p.
        Hack for LA is the official Los Angeles chapter of Code for America, a national nonprofit that believes government can work for the people, by the people, in the 21st century. We bring together coders, designers, entrepreneurs, students, government staff, activists, and other civic-minded people to solve the LA region’s biggest civic challenges.
      #contact
        h3 Contact Us
        p.
          Are you press and want to get in touch? Are you interested in becoming a sponsor? Want to just #[a(href='http://hackforla-slack.herokuapp.com/', target='_blank') check us out on Slack]? Looking to volunteer?
        form.js-ajax-form.contact-form(action='thank-you', method='post', name='Contact Form', netlify)
          textarea(placeholder='Send us a message', name='message', required)
          .form-controls
            .form-input
              label(for='contact-email').sr-only Enter your email address
              input(type='email',
                name='email',
                placeholder='Enter your email address', required)#contact-email
            button(type='submit').btn.btn-primary Send message
          p.form-confirmation.hidden Thanks! You'll hear from us soon.
